006.","meanings":["From Old Norse, originally a byname meaning ‘bride, wife’; in mythology the name of Thor's golden-haired wife."],"variants":[]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir William Bucke was born in 1400, his father, John Bucke, was 65 and his mother, Isabell Hall, was 57. He married Lady Isabel Hall about 1420, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1460, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1400–1460":"1400–1460","1405–1480":"1405–1480","1430–Male":"1430–Surnud","1445–Male":"1445–Surnud","1335–Male":"1335–Surnud","1344–Female":"1344–Surnud","       1445":"1445","before 1400":"enne 1400","1335":"1335","1445":"1445","1400":"1400","Abt 1420":"umbes 1420","1344":"1344","1430":"1430","1460":"1460","1480":"1480","1405":"1405","Melford, Suffolk, England":"Long Melford, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"1400–1460":"1400–1460","1405–1480":"1405–1480","1430–Male":"1430–Kuollut","1445–Male":"1445–Kuollut","1335–Male":"1335–Kuollut","1344–Female":"1344–Kuollut","       1445":"1445","before 1400":"ennen vuotta 1400","1335":"1335","1445":"1445","1400":"1400","Abt 1420":"noin 1420","1344":"1344","1430":"1430","1460":"1460","1480":"1480","1405":"1405","Melford, Su